result.formatted_address: 6號 Pak Sha Rd, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Tai Ping Koon Restaurant

reviews.text:
We always try to come here just for their Soufflé. It’s huge and the size of your head.. 

Lots of history in this restaurant, it’s a blast from the past and the waiters are dressed in the same uniform styled from the 60s.

We came during Happy Hour as the price is more palatable for the Soufflé Set. We also ordered the Beef Flat Rice Noodle with Swiss (sweet Soy) sauce.

Service is impeccable and the food is tasty.
People come to this restaurant for a trip down memory lane. Used to be an acclaimed western restaurant with a Hong Kong twist some  3-4 decades ago. The food is just so so. Too oily and sweet for me.

A very nice traditional Hong Kong Style restaurant which offers some signature dishes where you cannot find elsewhere. However, please don;t count it as a Western restaurant but a localize one instead. The stirred fried beef with flat rice noodles is one you should try. The boiled OX tongue is also delicious and you should have a try. For the dessert menu, you do not have many choices but the soffle is good enough.
Not bad if you like your food on the salty side
Their chicken wing super nice.. Must try
